### 10. **sas_functions.py** - SAS Compatibility

```python
from COMMON.sas_functions import left, upcase, translate, substr, mdy, put

# String functions
df['NAME'] = left(df['NAME'])              # Remove leading spaces
df['NAME'] = upcase(df['NAME'])            # Convert to uppercase
df['GRADE'] = translate(df['GRADE'], '[]', '××')  # Replace characters

# Substring (1-based indexing like SAS)
df['PRODUCT'] = substr(df['FACCODE'], 6, 5)  # Start at position 6, length 5

# Date creation
date_obj = mdy(10, 23, 2025)  # October 23, 2025

# Formatting
formatted = put(12345, 'COMMA15.2')  # "12,345.00"
formatted = put(date_obj, 'DDMMYY8')  # "23102025"
```

