### 11. **data_transform.py** - ETL Patterns

```python
from COMMON.data_transform import (
    apply_sas_formats,
    merge_datasets,
    deduplicate,
    filter_approved,
    left_align_columns,
    set_default_values
)

# Apply SAS formats to DataFrame
df = apply_sas_formats(df, col_types, col_subtypes, col_decimals)

# Filter for APPROVED status
df = filter_approved(df, status_col='STATUS')

# Remove duplicates (NODUPKEY)
df = deduplicate(df, subset='AANO', keep='first')

# Merge multiple datasets (SAS MERGE)
merged = merge_datasets([df1, df2, df3], on='AANO', how='outer')

# Left-align columns (SAS LEFT function)
df = left_align_columns(df, ['REFINANC', 'SECTCD2', 'STATUS'])

# Set defaults (IF col='' THEN col='0')
df = set_default_values(df, {'DNBFISME': '0'})
```

